== Overview

These notes correspond to *CSGY-6003: Foundations of Computer Science*, a graduate-level
course at New York University. The course provides a rigorous introduction to the
mathematical foundations underlying modern computer science, with emphasis on
formal reasoning, abstraction, and correctness.

The material emphasizes precise definitions, proofs, and models that are essential
for advanced study in algorithms, programming languages, systems, and theory.

*Course focus includes:*
Discrete mathematical structures, logic, proof techniques, automata and formal
languages, computability, and an introduction to computational complexity.

